00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:30.050
I did it to myself.

00:39:30.050 --> 00:39:32.460
There's no need.

00:39:32.460 --> 00:39:36.860
So now we're going to just talk
about how meditation can really

00:39:36.860 --> 00:39:42.540
help us bring our mind to a
healthier, stronger place,

00:39:42.540 --> 00:39:46.390
so we can function from a place
of strength and not weakness.

00:39:46.390 --> 00:39:48.450
Imagine living your
whole life without really

00:39:48.450 --> 00:39:51.390
taking care of your mind.

00:39:51.390 --> 00:39:55.680
So what meditation does for the
mind, it nourishes the mind.

00:39:55.680 --> 00:39:58.260
So we have our
physical body, and we

00:39:58.260 --> 00:40:00.500
take care of our
physical body how?

00:40:00.500 --> 00:40:04.274
By exercising, by
eating properly,

00:40:04.274 --> 00:40:10.150
but the control center is
up here for the whole body.

00:40:10.150 --> 00:40:13.180
And we're not doing anything
about the control center.

00:40:13.180 --> 00:40:16.500
It's like cleaning the car,
but letting the engine just

00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:17.790
fall apart.

00:40:17.790 --> 00:40:19.380
Think about it for a moment.

00:40:19.380 --> 00:40:22.349
That's the control center,
and when was the last time

00:40:22.349 --> 00:40:24.890
we actually sat down-- oh, we've
got to take care of the mind

00:40:24.890 --> 00:40:26.570
right now?

00:40:26.570 --> 00:40:27.840
No one tells us to do that.

00:40:27.840 --> 00:40:28.430
We've forgotten it.

00:40:28.430 --> 00:40:29.804
Out of sight, out
of mind, right?

00:40:29.804 --> 00:40:32.010
That's kind of what's happening.

00:40:32.010 --> 00:40:34.715
So meditation-- it's an
exercise for the mind.

00:40:34.715 --> 00:40:37.310
It makes the mind your friend.

00:40:37.310 --> 00:40:40.670
And it helps you develop
positive perspectives.

00:40:40.670 --> 00:40:42.870
So when you meditate,
your mind wanders.

00:40:42.870 --> 00:40:44.090
You have to bring it back.

00:40:44.090 --> 00:40:44.620
It wanders.

00:40:44.620 --> 00:40:45.870
You have to bring it back.

00:40:45.870 --> 00:40:47.440
And that's an exercise.

00:40:47.440 --> 00:40:49.710
Kind of like pushups
for the mind.

00:40:49.710 --> 00:40:51.990
So the more we
exercise the mind,

00:40:51.990 --> 00:40:53.730
we take time out
on a regular basis

00:40:53.730 --> 00:40:56.170
to do that, the
healthier it'll become.

00:40:56.170 --> 00:40:59.800
We'll feel the effects
of depression and anxiety

00:40:59.800 --> 00:41:00.910
decreasing.

00:41:00.910 --> 00:41:03.682
We'll feel having more
positive perspective.

00:41:03.682 --> 00:41:05.140
Something difficult
happens, you'll

00:41:05.140 --> 00:41:06.910
be able to see that as
an opportunity for growth

00:41:06.910 --> 00:41:08.659
instead of just diving
into it and staying

00:41:08.659 --> 00:41:11.076
depressed for the next
couple weeks about it.

00:41:11.076 --> 00:41:12.450
It all depends on
a healthy mind,

00:41:12.450 --> 00:41:15.370
and this is the way
to really do it.

00:41:15.370 --> 00:41:18.060
Through the positive
perspective, helping you

00:41:18.060 --> 00:41:21.260
see the glass as half full
and not as half empty.

00:41:21.260 --> 00:41:22.860
The really great
quote here that I

00:41:22.860 --> 00:41:24.959
like from Steve Jobs,
