I decided to turn my
journal into a book,

00:58:04.280 --> 00:58:08.160
because I thought maybe that me
sharing my story would inspire

00:58:08.160 --> 00:58:10.780
others to, perhaps, also turn
towards your spirituality

00:58:10.780 --> 00:58:12.450
in difficult times.

00:58:12.450 --> 00:58:15.110
The book goes through my
own journey growing up

00:58:15.110 --> 00:58:18.240
in Southern California
where my parents lose

00:58:18.240 --> 00:58:21.470
their multi-million
dollar business, which

00:58:21.470 --> 00:58:24.260
forces us to move
to East Europe.

00:58:24.260 --> 00:58:27.030
Being so uprooted from
my society and my culture

00:58:27.030 --> 00:58:28.800
and my lifestyle
that I had in LA,

00:58:28.800 --> 00:58:31.860
it was a very difficult
time, a very uncertain time.

00:58:31.860 --> 00:58:34.360
And so I decided to explore
the Bhagavad Gita, one

00:58:34.360 --> 00:58:36.805
of the main spiritual
texts of India

00:58:36.805 --> 00:58:40.050
to understand why all
this is happening to me.

00:58:40.050 --> 00:58:42.160
Why am I suffering so intensely?

00:58:42.160 --> 00:58:44.180
And at that moment, the
Bhagavad Gita really

00:58:44.180 --> 00:58:46.470
gave me the answers
that I was looking for.

00:58:46.470 --> 00:58:47.260
It gave me solace.

00:58:47.260 --> 00:58:49.220
It actually gave me hope.

00:58:49.220 --> 00:58:51.970
A lot of times when people
go through difficulties

00:58:51.970 --> 00:58:55.820
in their lives, we
just become fixated

00:58:55.820 --> 00:58:58.260
on trying to fix the problem.

00:58:58.260 --> 00:59:00.610
Find a quick solution,
so the suffering

00:59:00.610 --> 00:59:02.950
goes away, so the
pain goes away.

00:59:02.950 --> 00:59:05.180
However, that's
not really getting

00:59:05.180 --> 00:59:09.327
to the core of the problem,
which is deep within side.

00:59:09.327 --> 00:59:10.910
One of the things I
try to help people

00:59:10.910 --> 00:59:14.380
understand is the
nature of their own mind

00:59:14.380 --> 00:59:16.660
and that if we can
actually nourish the mind,

00:59:16.660 --> 00:59:18.385
feed the mind
through meditation,

00:59:18.385 --> 00:59:20.910
and exercise the mind--
because when you meditate,

00:59:20.910 --> 00:59:23.720
the mind wanders, and you know
that it just went somewhere.

00:59:23.720 --> 00:59:26.280
Then you have to bring it
back, and that bringing it

00:59:26.280 --> 00:59:28.237
back is an exercise.

00:59:28.237 --> 00:59:30.570
It's like I like to think of
it as pushups for the mind.

00:59:30.570 --> 00:59:32.410
What I'm really
hoping is that people

00:59:32.410 --> 00:59:34.760
will be inspired
through this book

00:59:34.760 --> 00:59:37.785
to give their spirituality
a serious chance

00:59:37.785 --> 00:59:39.160
not only when
they're struggling,

00:59:39.160 --> 00:59:41.570
but when things are good also.

00:59:41.570 --> 00:59:44.470
Just to keep it as much
a part of their life

00:59:44.470 --> 00:59:46.860
as breakfast, lunch, and dinner.

00:59:46.860 --> 00:59:51.560
Make spirituality a part
of the everyday experience.

